<p>All calculations are strictly based on commonly used budgeting formulas. Please consult financial advisors for personalized advice.</p>
<h2>The Formula Explained</h2>
<p class="formula-box">Total Cost = Monthly Hobby Cost Ã— Number of Months</p>
<h2>Glossary of Terms</h2>
<ul>
<li><strong>Monthly Hobby Cost:</strong> The estimated expense for your hobby per month.</li>
<li><strong>Number of Months:</strong> The duration you plan to pursue the hobby.</li>
<li><strong>Total Cost:</strong> The cumulative expense over the selected months.</li>
</ul>
<h2>How It Works: A Step-by-Step Example</h2>
<p>Enter the monthly cost of your hobby and the number of months you plan to engage in it. For instance, if your hobby costs $100 per month and you plan to continue for 6 months, the total cost will be $600.</p>
